      Can you use Instagram logo?
      BRAND GUIDELINES AND ASSETS

      Only those planning to use Instagram's assets in any broadcast, radio, out-of-home advertising or print larger than 8.5 x 11 inches (A4 size) need to request permission. Requests must be in English and include a mock of how you're planning to use the Instagram logo.

      Is there an Instagram logo Emoji?
      Emoji Details

      This open source emoji is named "instagram" and is licensed under the open source CC BY 4.0 license. It's also a defined emoji, which means it's part of the open standard on emojis. It's available to be downloaded in SVG and PNG formats (available in 256, 512, 1024 and 2048 PNG sizes).

      What is the new Instagram symbol?
      The new Instagram logo depicts a camera, but in the most minimal way, with just a square, a circle, and a dot. However, true to the first logo, it's not a contemporary camera—it's an old, 1970s or 80s, Polaroid-type camera, carrying connotations of nostalgia, childhood, family photos, and so on.
